# Architecture (NON-NEGOTIABLE)

## Client-Only

This is a fully client-side application. No backend, no API calls, no database.

- Do NOT create a backend server, REST API, or database
- Do NOT make network requests from the app (except static asset loading)
- Do NOT import or use `fetch()` for data operations
- All state lives in the browser: `useReducer` state + `sessionStorage` checkpoints
- Deployment is static files served by Vercel

## Single Source of Truth

The `LessonState` managed by `useReducer` is the ONLY source of truth.

- Visual components are pure projections of `LessonState` — they NEVER own state
- Fraction blocks render FROM engine state, never the reverse
- During drag animations, use CSS transforms for preview only — commit state change only on gesture completion
- The reducer rejects impossible state transitions (denominator > 12, invalid fractions)

## Deterministic Math

The `FractionEngine` is the sole authority on mathematical correctness.

- The LLM / scripted dialogue NEVER evaluates math — `FractionEngine.areEquivalent()` is the only judge
- `EvaluationResult.isCorrect` is always computed by the engine, never by text matching or LLM output
- All engine functions are pure (same input → same output, no side effects, no network)
- The `TutorBrain` interface separates pedagogy from math — implementations can change, the engine stays

## State Flow

```
User Action → Reducer (validates via Engine) → New LessonState → React re-render → Visual update
```

Never shortcut this flow. Never mutate state outside the reducer.
